sentences.english: Once again park well away from the area.
sentences.chinese: 再说一遍，把车停得远远的。

sentences.english: It was after dark and I was nervous, so when he pulled up I immediately jumped in the car.
sentences.chinese: 天黑了，我很紧张，看到车过来了就跳上去。

sentences.english: They towed the van to the church parking lot for safekeeping.
sentences.chinese: 他们把箱型车拖到教会的停车场保管。

sentences.english: I parked in the lot at Central High.
sentences.chinese: 我把车停在了中央高中的停车场。

sentences.english: The role of lead car has been rotated which is great and a bit of fun.
sentences.chinese: 领队的车已被旋转的作用是一个伟大的一点乐趣。

sentences.english: American prefer buying Japs car and third world consumer goods.
sentences.chinese: 日本人喜欢买美国车和第三世界的消费品。

sentences.english: Presently, Topics of cars are hanging on my lips. One in three words escaping from my lips has something to do with cars.
sentences.chinese: 现在，嘴边常常念叨着车，三句话离不开车的话题。

sentences.english: Presently, Topics of cars are hanging on my lips. One in three words escaping from my lips has something to do with cars.
sentences.chinese: 现在，嘴边常常念叨着车，三句话离不开车的话题。

sentences.english: At about half the distance to Zunyi, I came across a long line of cars.
sentences.chinese: 大约在去遵义的半道上我碰上了一串车排起了长龙。
警官，我的车后部被撞了。

sentences.english: And a big number of cars are still sold around the world because of their look.
sentences.chinese: 而世界上很多车依然是在卖外观。

sentences.english: The car must break down just when we were about to start off.
sentences.chinese: 我们正要出发时偏偏车又坏了。

sentences.english: We stop at Pin Wu for lunch, but Sam and David never come down.
sentences.chinese: 中途，司机在平武停下车吃午饭，鹏和嫣没有下车。

sentences.english: It takes just 25 minutes to make the 75-mile trip.
sentences.chinese: 仅仅25分钟，车就行驶75英里。

sentences.english: See the picture, this PT Cruiser has chrome front bumper and hubcaps.
sentences.chinese: 这辆车的前保险杠和轮盖都是电镀的。

sentences.english: Park the car in the driveway so it's off the street.
sentences.chinese: 把车停在车道上，要开时便可以直接通到马路。
